potential_friends.bio: Craig Agranoff is an, entrepreneur, and a noted national Social Media consultant as well as noted specialist in online reputation management and monitoring. He has worked with many internet startups and founded the tech blog sCommerce.com and edits Rev2.org. You can also find his writing as the Tech/Social Media Correspondent in the Boca News, The New Times,VentureBeat.com, and reviews.vois. Craig has been featured in Miami Herald, New Times, The Palm Beach Post, AOL Digital Cities, Slice, CenterNetworks, Thrillist and The Sun-Sentinel. You can also view his appearances on Gary Vaynerchuck's Wine Library Tv, Fox News, and CBS News. He is a frequent speaker at tech events such as Refresh,New Tech Community, Bar Camp and LaidOffCamp. He was also nominated for one his recent ventures at Mashable’s Open Web Awards as a finalist for best Large Scale Social Network, winning best “Photo Sharing Website Category”. Furthermore, Craig is the Pizza Expert.
